headline: A Fresh Look at Accenture (ACN) Valuation Following Major Institutional Exit and Slower Growth Concerns
summary: Accenture (ACN) is in the spotlight after a major institutional investor exited its position. This move reflects ongoing concerns around decelerating growth and weaker demand for consulting services. The news follows the company's recent earnings report. See our latest analysis for Accenture. It has been a bumpy year for Accenture, with the share price down 27.5% year-to-date and the 1-year total shareholder return falling 29.4%.
